Date: 27/9/1906
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: The honourable member will probably recall the suggestion made in the last paragraph of my reply to a somewhat similar question asked by the member for Dunedin North on the 29th August - the suggestion namely, to publish a school journal which would contain matter suitable to take the place of the supplementary readers required in the various standards. This suggestion is now being considered, and, if it be found possible to give effect to it, I believe the result will be a considerable reduction, at all events, of the hardships now said to be entailed by frequent changes in the class-books used in the schools.
